{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2012/02/html5-and-css3-boilerplate-files/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"J. Pedro Ribeiro"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"1c08c4f3-4307-5b4b-aa77-cabccb55d54c","excerpt":"Boilerplate is a set of files composed to be used over and over again. In front-end development (any area actually), starting from scratch every time you have a…","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7ca682fc9d10f89ec413979e68fda5e1/80e3c/boilerplate.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.34177215189873%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"boilerplate\"\n        title=\"boilerplate\"\n        src=\"/static/7ca682fc9d10f89ec413979e68fda5e1/828fb/boilerplate.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7ca682fc9d10f89ec413979e68fda5e1/ff44c/boilerplate.jpg 158w,\n/static/7ca682fc9d10f89ec413979e68fda5e1/a6688/boilerplate.jpg 315w,\n/static/7ca682fc9d10f89ec413979e68fda5e1/828fb/boilerplate.jpg 630w,\n/static/7ca682fc9d10f89ec413979e68fda5e1/80e3c/boilerplate.jpg 720w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>Boilerplate</strong> is a set of files composed to be used over and over again. In <a href=\"http://jpedroribeiro.com/tag/front-end-development/\">front-end development</a> (any area actually), starting from scratch every time you have a new <strong>project</strong> is a waste of time and money. How many times have you reset your css or applied the same basic styles to the same <a href=\"http://jpedroribeiro.com/tag/html/\">html</a> tags?</p>\n<p>There are a vast amount of boilerplate files out there. Some are very complex and full of options, other are focused to certain types of projects. You are very well served of options.</p>\n<p>On the projects I work on, I prefer to use a something simpler but that covers most of the areas. I <strong>created this set</strong> based on what I use the most.</p>\n<h2>The Boilerplate</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 465px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f4472a6efd2a13fd9ffc7bd95cd378ef/9ff85/html5boilerplate.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 11.39240506329114%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"html5boilerplate\"\n        title=\"html5boilerplate\"\n        src=\"/static/f4472a6efd2a13fd9ffc7bd95cd378ef/9ff85/html5boilerplate.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f4472a6efd2a13fd9ffc7bd95cd378ef/c26ae/html5boilerplate.png 158w,\n/static/f4472a6efd2a13fd9ffc7bd95cd378ef/6bdcf/html5boilerplate.png 315w,\n/static/f4472a6efd2a13fd9ffc7bd95cd378ef/9ff85/html5boilerplate.png 465w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 465px) 100vw, 465px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This set is not 100% original. Like almost everything <strong>web</strong> related, it is a combination of several others plus my own insights resulting on what works for me. I use some of <a href=\"http://meyerweb.com/eric/tools/css/reset/\">Eric Meyers CSS Reset</a>, mixed with some details by <a href=\"http://html5doctor.com/html-5-boilerplates/\">HTML Doctor</a>, <a href=\"http://html5boilerplate.com/\">HTML5 Boilerplate</a> and others. You are welcome to make your additions, updates and customise it to fit your requirements.</p>\n<h2>HTML</h2>\n<p>Start out creating a basic <strong>HTML5</strong> file. Add <a href=\"http://www.modernizr.com/\">Modernizr</a> (on header) so we can use new html5 tags on older <strong>browsers</strong> plus it allow us to detect whether the browser support css3 or not (always useful for graceful degradations).</p>\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n<p>Do a basic <strong>css reset</strong> and minify it to make it stand out from your own styles, plus it will save you some bytes. If you are making a <strong>Wordpress</strong> theme, don't forget to add your details as comments on top, I recommend adding those details anyway. Add <strong>conditional comments</strong> to place your IE8- styles. If you are going <a href=\"http://jpedroribeiro.com/tag/responsive/\">responsive</a> (and you should!) place stylesheets according to the devices/screens you are going to support. Plus the <strong>print</strong> stylesheet.</p>\n<h2>Scripts</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 237px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cf74c93d657f71c692a9cc1eddff23a5/008e2/jquery.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 22.78481012658228%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"jquery\"\n        title=\"jquery\"\n        src=\"/static/cf74c93d657f71c692a9cc1eddff23a5/008e2/jquery.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cf74c93d657f71c692a9cc1eddff23a5/c26ae/jquery.png 158w,\n/static/cf74c93d657f71c692a9cc1eddff23a5/008e2/jquery.png 237w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 237px) 100vw, 237px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Add the latest <a href=\"http://jquery.com/\">jQuery</a> for advanced javascript support. You can get it either from Google repository or download and use the latest version (I prefer this, I don't like to rely on others, even Google!). Add a Site.js (or whatever name you want) to host your own javascript and jQuery calls. These all should be on the <strong>bottom</strong> of your HTML document (we only leave Modernizr on top to enable HTML5 on old browsers).</p>\n<h2>Everything Else</h2>\n<p><strong>Favicon</strong> and <strong>iPad/iPhone</strong> icons also should be provided (on top of HTML doc). You can also add your own <strong>meta</strong> information. Not only good for <strong>SEO</strong>, it works as a signature of your project. Speaking of meta, add viewport and set it for mobile devices if you're going responsive.</p>\n<h2>Wrap Up</h2>\n<p>This is how I basically created my <strong>boilerplate</strong>, you can download it here and see it in action. It has folder structure to help organize the files and speed up maintenance.</p>\n<p>Bear in mind this is always work in progress, so make sure to come back and check the upcoming updates.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://jpedroribeiro.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/v2.0-2011-blank-template.rar\">DOWNLOAD THE FILES</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"HTML5 and CSS3 Boilerplate files","date":"February 28, 2012"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2012/02/html5-and-css3-boilerplate-files/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2012/02/css-only-drop-down-menu/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"CSS Only Drop Down Menu","tags":null}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2012/05/html5-css3-curriculum-vitae-resume-template/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"HTML5 & CSS3 Curriculum Vitae (Résumé) Template","tags":["html","css","curriculum"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454","792910177"],"slicesMap":{}}